2026-05-26 | Count Special Letters

	Question
Return number of special letters.
	Key Insight
We only need to know:
		which lowercase letters exist
		and which uppercase letters exist.
Then compare both.
	Approach
1.	Create two sets:
		lowercase letters
		uppercase letters
2.	Traverse string:
		if lowercase:
				store in lower set
		else:
				store lowercase equivalent
				in upper set
3.	Count letters present in both sets.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	(at most 26 letters)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfSpecialChars(string word) {
        unordered_set<char> lower;
        unordered_set<char> upper;
        for(char c : word){
            if(islower(c)){
                lower.insert(c);
            }
            else{
                upper.insert(tolower(c));
            }
        }
        int count = 0;
        for(char c : lower){
            if(upper.count(c))
                count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
	Key Insight
A character becomes special only if:
		both versions of same alphabet exist.  
Hash sets make this checking simple and efficient.
